headline: Costco Execs Have Been Selling Stock on the Heels of a Rough 2025
summary: Two  Costco Wholesale  executives sold a combined $3.7 million worth of company stock over the past several weeks, while another insider is gearing up to make a sale.  Russ Miller, a senior executive vice president, sold 1,500 shares on Jan. 9 for $916.32 apiece, according to a Form 4 filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on Monday.  Costco announced Miller’s retirement, effective February, late last year.

headline: Costco quietly speeds up checkout with two major changes
